## 🚀 Example

### Input

```text
n = 3
l = 1
r = 3
```

Possible zig-zag arrays:

```text
1 2 1
1 3 1
1 3 2
2 1 2
2 3 1
3 2 1
...
```

The matrix exponentiation computes the total count of all valid sequences.

---

## ⏱️ Complexity Analysis

Let:

```text
k = r - l + 1
```

Number of states:

```text
S = 2k
```

### Matrix Multiplication

```text
O(S³)
```

### Binary Exponentiation

```text
O(log n)
```

multiplications.

### Overall

```text
O((2k)³ log n)
= O(k³ log n)
```

---

### Space Complexity

The matrices require:

```text
O((2k)²)
```

memory.

